featured.text: I had just arrived by plane and still had jetlag.

definition.zh_def: 因跨越多個時區而導致的身體不適，通常表現為疲倦、失眠和注意力不集中。
definition.en_def: A temporary condition resulting from traveling across multiple time zones, characterized by fatigue, insomnia, and difficulty concentrating.
definition.example: After flying to Japan, I experienced severe jetlag for several days.
